<br>
Sure, you meet some frustrating ones, like a quest NPC not working or an astral projection not giving you the flags you deserve after kiling a mob, or an uber mob dropping cloth caps or no loot whatsoever, but if that's all the setbacks you face you're many times better than the guilds that come after you.  You know, those who have to deal with abhorrable drop rates, harder mobs, competition with other guilds, and mob triggers being blown by the pioneering guilds in order to starve those who follow.  <br>
<br>
The true rewards of pioneering should be the pride of knowing you were the first, access to the loot of mobs before others, knowing how to beat them and thus getting more shots at them, and becoming thus equipped to go even further than anyone did before.  They are not the byproducts of VI's lack of testing, or the exploitation thus spawned.<br>
